Variation in specimens. Strength of and distance between axial lamellae vary. Color varies considerably, from unicolor to spotted (color form
acerbulum
). The degree of expansion of the outer lip also varies but is usually narrow. Specimens from Belize are smaller than specimens from elsewhere.
